The paper discusses the use of Function-as-a-Service (FaaS) for running scientific workflows on cloud infrastructure. This involves evaluating the performance of FaaS providers such as Amazon, Google, and IBM, as well as analyzing aspects related to infrastructure provisioning, API overhead, and run time accounting. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are Distributed and Parallel Computing (cs.DC), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Scientific Computing (cs.SC), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
